abstract: Dougherty County, Ga, district attorney Greg Edwards drops murder charge against Kenlissia Jones, who is accused of ending her pregnancy with abortion pill obtained without prescription; Edwards is pursuing drug possession count against Jones.
lead_paragraph: A prosecutor dropped a murder charge Wednesday but is pursuing a drug possession count against a woman accused of ending her pregnancy without a prescription, using pills she bought online.

headline.main: Georgia: No Murder Charge for Woman Who Bought Abortion Pills Online
headline.print_headline: Georgia: No Murder Charge for Woman Who Bought Abortion Pills Online
